      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To quantify P(s) at sub-kilobase resolution (Fig 2), cooltools avoids conversion from sparse-to-dense matrices. Instead, the calculation is done by iterating over chunks of pixels stored in coolers, assigning pixels to regions, and aggregating at each distance. ... To reduce variation at large genomic separations due to increasing sparsity of the data, cooltools returns P(s) curves smoothed in log-space using a numba-accelerated approach.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes P(s) calculation and log-space smoothing but does not name a specific function called 'logbin_expected'. The paper discusses the general approach to computing and smoothing P(s) curves, but the specific function name 'logbin_expected' is not mentioned in the provided passages.",
