      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms cooltools computes coverage (cis/total) but does NOT explicitly describe export to bedGraph or CSV/TSV formats. The paper states cooltools 'provides a paired command line interface (CLI) and Python application programming interface (API)' and 'accepts pandas dataframes, while the CLI reuses existing formats when possible: BED-like files for interval data and bedgraphs or bigwigs for genomic tracks' [passage 5], but this refers to INPUT formats, not export outputs. No evidence of bedGraph/CSV export functionality for coverage tracks.",
