    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/eigenvector-digitization-into-compartment-bins/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Since eigenvectors are determined only up to a sign and compartmentalization patterns are sometimes better captured by second or third eigenvectors, calculated vectors often need to be oriented and sorted according to their correlation with known markers of activity (e.g., GC content, density of genes). Cooltools allows users to request an arbitrary number of eigenvectors and can sort and orient eigenvectors according to a provided \"phasing track\", most commonly the GC content per genomic bin.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes eigenvector extraction and orientation but does not explicitly name a 'digitize' function. However, the downstream saddle plot analysis requires discrete binning of compartment profiles.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pcbi-1012067",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "eigenvector-digitization-into-compartment-bins",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Discretize continuous eigenvector values from Hi-C compartment analysis into categorical bins (typically 2\u20135 levels) representing A/B compartment states using quantile or fixed thresholds.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:03:08.276592+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/eigenvector-digitization-into-compartment-bins/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Bins can be assigned to classes either by discrete properties, or by discretizing a quantitative signal. cooltools operates on observed-over-expected contact frequencies, either based on raw counts or balanced data, and can be restricted to either cis or trans portions of the genome wide map.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly describes discretizing quantitative signals (eigenvectors) into classes for saddle plot analysis.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pcbi-1012067",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "eigenvector-digitization-into-compartment-bins",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "This preprocessing step converts a continuous genomic track into a discrete compartment assignment required for downstream saddle plot analysis and compartment interaction quantification.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:03:08.276592+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/eigenvector-digitization-into-compartment-bins/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Bins can be assigned to classes either by discrete properties, or by discretizing a quantitative signal.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes discretization of quantitative signals (eigenvectors) into classes for saddle analysis, but does not explicitly name a function called 'digitize'. The paper states cooltools performs this discretization but the specific function name is not confirmed in the passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pcbi-1012067",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "eigenvector-digitization-into-compartment-bins",
