    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/genomic-coordinate-conversion/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Cooltools provides a paired command line interface (CLI) and Python application programming interface (API)... Cooltools leverages the widely-adopted cooler format which handles storage and access for high-resolution datasets.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes cooltools and cooler as tools for Hi-C analysis and data storage, but does not explicitly discuss 'converting genomic coordinates between reference frames' or 'mapping bin indices to genomic intervals' as a primary research question or use case. The paper focuses on feature extraction (compartments, insulation, dots) and quantification from contact maps, not coordinate conversion workflows.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pcbi-1012067",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "genomic-coordinate-conversion",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Convert genomic coordinates between reference frames or extract region-specific Hi-C data by mapping bin indices to genomic intervals",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:03:22.667561+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/genomic-coordinate-conversion/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Cooler handles storage and access for high-resolution datasets via a sparse data model... the cooler storage format and library, which allows it to operate on sparse matrices and/or out-of-core, either on raw counts or normalized contact matrices.",
      "asbval:note": "Cooler is confirmed as the storage format and library for Hi-C data. The paper confirms cooler stores binned contact data, which inherently requires a bin table with genomic coordinates.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pcbi-1012067",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "genomic-coordinate-conversion",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "cooler \u2014 Provides bin table and cooler file I/O; bin table contains chrom, start, end coordinates used to map bin indices to genomic positions",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:03:22.667561+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/genomic-coordinate-conversion/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Insulation profiles quantify the frequency of contacts across each genomic bin averaged over a sliding diamond-shaped window... Cooltools detects insulating boundaries as local minima of the insulation profile and quantifies their strength as their topographic prominence.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly describes cooltools computing per-bin metrics (insulation scores, boundary calls). The output is bin-indexed and must be linked to genomic coordinates for downstream use.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pcbi-1012067",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "genomic-coordinate-conversion",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "cooltools \u2014 Computes per-bin metrics (insulation scores, boundary calls) that must be mapped back to genomic coordinates via the cooler bin table",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:03:22.667561+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/genomic-coordinate-conversion/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Return widely-used Python data structures, pandas dataframes, and numpy arrays, for user-facing outputs... Cooltools delegates to numpy, scipy, and pandas when possible and aims to follow the style of these APIs.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms cooltools returns pandas DataFrames as outputs and leverages pandas for data operations. This supports the use of pandas for coordinate mapping and export.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pcbi-1012067",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "genomic-coordinate-conversion",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "pandas \u2014 DataFrame join/merge operations to associate bin indices with genomic coordinates and export to tabular formats",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
