      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/hi-c-coverage-track-computation/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Cooltools enables users to extract key features seen in 3C maps, including: the decay of contact frequency with genomic distance, plaid patterns of active and inactive compartments, domains, and dots... The methods in cooltools are modular and provide access to both high-level and low-level APIs.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms cooltools provides modular tools for insulation, compartments (saddles), and other downstream analyses. Coverage is presented as a foundational tool.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pcbi-1012067",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "hi-c-coverage-track-computation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Use it before downstream Hi-C computations (e.g., insulation, contact scaling, saddle point analysis) that may be confounded by uneven sequencing depth.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:03:40.604317+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/hi-c-expected-value-calculation/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Contact frequency decreases rapidly with genomic separation within chromosomes, which arises because chromosomes are long polymers. This feature is interchangeably referred to as the: (i) expected because locus-specific features increase or decrease contact frequency relative to this major trend, (ii) scaling which is borrowed from the polymer physics literature, (iii) P(s), or contact probability, P, as a function of genomic separation, s.",
      "asbval:note": "Verbatim match: 'expected' as null model for P(s); passage describes expected as baseline for normalizing contact frequency by distance.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pcbi-1012067",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "hi-c-expected-value-calculation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Compute expected contact frequency as a function of genomic distance from a Hi-C contact matrix, producing a distance-binned expected value table that serves as a null model for detecting significant interactions and normalizing contact probability P(s) curves.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:03:51.608825+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/hi-c-expected-value-calculation/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Cooltools leverages the widely-adopted cooler format which handles storage and access for high-resolution datasets. Cooler handles storage and access for high-resolution datasets via a sparse data model.",
      "asbval:note": "Cooler confirmed as storage format for Hi-C matrices; passage [4] confirms cooler library provides foundation for cooltools analysis.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pcbi-1012067",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "hi-c-expected-value-calculation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "cooler \u2014 Library for storing and querying Hi-C contact matrices in HDF5-based format; provides bin indexing and bin-pair iteration required for expected value summation.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:03:51.608825+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/hi-c-expected-value-calculation/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To quantify P(s) at sub-kilobase resolution (Fig 2), cooltools avoids conversion from sparse-to-dense matrices. Instead, the calculation is done by iterating over chunks of pixels stored in coolers, assigning pixels to regions, and aggregating at each distance... cooltools returns P(s) curves smoothed in log-space using a numba-accelerated approach.",
      "asbval:note": "Verbatim: cooltools computes expected/P(s) with log-space smoothing; passage describes the expected module functionality for distance-binned contact frequency calculation.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pcbi-1012067",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "hi-c-expected-value-calculation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "cooltools \u2014 Python package providing the expected module and logbin_expected function for computing and smoothing expected contact frequency tables from cooler inputs.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:03:51.608825+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/hi-c-expected-value-calculation/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Here we introduce cooltools (https://github.com/open2c/cooltools), a suite of computational tools that enables flexible, scalable, and reproducible analysis of high-resolution contact frequency data. Cooltools provides a paired command line interface (CLI) and Python application programming interface (API), which respectively facilitate workflows on high-performance computing clusters and in interactive analysis environments.",
      "asbval:note": "Cooltools is a Python package with Python API; passage confirms Python as the execution environment.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pcbi-1012067",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "hi-c-expected-value-calculation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Python \u2014 Programming language environment for executing cooltools and cooler workflows.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:03:51.608825+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/hi-c-expected-value-calculation/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Cooltools is built directly on top of the cooler storage format and library, which allows it to operate on sparse matrices and/or out-of-core, either on raw counts or normalized contact matrices.",
      "asbval:note": "Scope aligns with paper's description of cooltools operating on cooler-format matrices for baseline analysis.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pcbi-1012067",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "hi-c-expected-value-calculation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "You have a cooler-format Hi-C contact matrix and need to establish a genome-wide baseline contact frequency by genomic distance.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:03:51.608825+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/hi-c-expected-value-calculation/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To enable interoperability with downstream analyses that require accounting for P(s), cooltools defines an expected format with specifications and checks. This includes both pairs of regions within chromosomes (cis expected) or pairs of regions on different chromosomes (trans expected)... cooltools also enables P(s) calculation on raw data... cooltools returns P(s) curves smoothed in log-space.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes expected as enabling O/E normalization and P(s) smoothing; semantic equivalence to card's scope.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pcbi-1012067",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "hi-c-expected-value-calculation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "This is essential when you want to normalize observed contacts, compute O/E ratios, generate P(s) smoothing pipelines, or identify deviation from random polymer behavior.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:03:51.608825+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/hi-c-expected-value-calculation/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Pairwise summaries, obtained by averaging over pairs of regions assigned to a set of classes, are a straightforward way to quantify these preferences... cooltools operates on observed-over-expected contact frequencies, either based on raw counts or balanced data... Insulation profiles quantify the frequency of contacts across each genomic bin averaged over a sliding diamond-shaped window.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms expected is prerequisite for saddle plots and insulation; semantic alignment with card's workflow ordering.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pcbi-1012067",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "hi-c-expected-value-calculation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Use this skill before applying downstream analyses like saddle plots, insulation scoring, or contact probability smoothing.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:03:51.608825+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/hi-c-expected-value-calculation/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "Paper does not discuss minimum coverage thresholds or sparsity constraints for expected value calculation. This is a practical guideline not addressed in the passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pcbi-1012067",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "hi-c-expected-value-calculation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Your Hi-C dataset has extreme sparsity or low coverage (< 10 million valid contacts) \u2014 expected values will be unreliable and noise-dominated.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0007675"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
