    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/python-pandas-data-manipulation/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "cooltools returns P(s) curves smoothed in log-space using a numba-accelerated approach. This also allows cooltools to more robustly compute the derivative of P(s) and observed-over-expected maps.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes log-space smoothing of P(s) curves via cooltools, not manual pandas TSV manipulation. The card frames this as a pandas/TSV workflow, but the paper's actual approach uses cooltools' built-in P(s) calculation directly on cooler sparse matrices, not TSV import/export. Functional goal (smoothing contact frequency curves) is present, but the claimed workflow (TSV\u2192pandas\u2192binning\u2192export) is not the paper's method.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pcbi-1012067",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "python-pandas-data-manipulation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Use Python and pandas to load, transform, and export tabular datasets (TSV/CSV) containing precomputed genomic statistics, applying binning, smoothing, and aggregation operations to prepare contact frequency curves for downstream analysis.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:05:23.836457+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/python-pandas-data-manipulation/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "cooltools returns P(s) curves smoothed in log-space using a numba-accelerated approach. To quantify P(s) at sub-kilobase resolution (Fig 2), cooltools avoids conversion from sparse-to-dense matrices. Instead, the calculation is done by iterating over chunks of pixels stored in coolers, assigning pixels to regions, and aggregating at each distance.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms cooltools performs log-space smoothing of P(s) curves, but does not name a function called 'logbin_expected'. The paper describes the smoothing algorithm applied during P(s) calculation from raw cooler data, not a separate function for post-hoc binning of precomputed TSV tables. The functional role (log-binning and smoothing) is present but the specific function name and input format (precomputed TSV) are not confirmed.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pcbi-1012067",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "python-pandas-data-manipulation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "cooltools with role: Provides logbin_expected function for log-binning and smoothing of precomputed expected contact frequency tables",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:05:23.836457+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/python-pandas-data-manipulation/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Cooltools leverages the widely-adopted cooler format which handles storage and access for high-resolution datasets. Cooler handles storage and access for high-resolution datasets via a sparse data model.",
      "asbval:note": "Confirmed: cooler stores Hi-C data in HDF5 format (.cool/.mcool). Paper also mentions 'expected format with specifications' and expected tables (cis and trans) are core outputs of cooltools analysis.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pcbi-1012067",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "python-pandas-data-manipulation",
