      "asbval:note": "Paper does not describe a TSV input workflow. Instead, cooltools calculates P(s) directly from cooler sparse matrices. The paper does define an 'expected format with specifications' for output, but input is cooler objects, not TSV files with dist_bp/contact_frequency columns.",
