      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/saddle-matrix-computation-from-binned-tracks/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Pairwise summaries, obtained by averaging over pairs of regions assigned to a set of classes, are a straightforward way to quantify these preferences... For genome folding, these are most frequently used to quantify the strength of compartmentalization after assigning classes from the extracted compartment profile. The pattern of preferences revealed by this averaging (where contacts are disfavored between active and inactive chromatin) led to these summaries being referred to as \"saddle plots\"",
      "asbval:note": "Claim is directly supported by passage describing saddle plot computation for compartment interaction quantification.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pcbi-1012067",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "saddle-matrix-computation-from-binned-tracks",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Compute a 2D saddle matrix that aggregates Hi-C contact frequency by genomic compartment pair, quantifying A/B compartment interaction asymmetry",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:05:40.630076+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/saddle-matrix-computation-from-binned-tracks/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To quantify these preferences with cooltools saddle (Fig 4), the approach is to: (i) group bins with similar properties into classes, (ii) average over all map pixels specified by the bins in each pair of classes (i.e. for each pair of classes p, q, summarize the collection of pixels {A ij | i in p, j in q}). Bins can be assigned to classes either by discrete properties, or by discretizing a quantitative signal.",
      "asbval:note": "Passage explicitly describes the digitization and saddle computation workflow.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pcbi-1012067",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "saddle-matrix-computation-from-binned-tracks",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "transforms digitized eigenvector tracks (binned into discrete compartment categories) and a cooler Hi-C contact matrix into a saddle strength metric",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:05:40.630076+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
