      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To quantify these preferences with cooltools saddle (Fig 4), the approach is to: (i) group bins with similar properties into classes, (ii) average over all map pixels specified by the bins in each pair of classes... Bins can be assigned to classes either by discrete properties, or by discretizing a quantitative signal.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly names cooltools.saddle but does not explicitly name a 'cooltools.digitize' function. The paper describes discretization/binning as part of the workflow but does not confirm a specific function name 'digitize'. The digitization step is described as part of the saddle workflow but the specific function name is not verified in passages.",
